{"primaryContentSections":[{"kind":"declarations","declarations":[{"platforms":["macOS"],"languages":["swift"],"tokens":[{"text":"subscript","kind":"keyword"},{"text":"(","kind":"text"},{"text":"orKey","kind":"externalParam"},{"text":" ","kind":"text"},{"text":"key","kind":"internalParam"},{"text":": ","kind":"text"},{"kind":"typeIdentifier","text":"Key"},{"text":") -> ","kind":"text"},{"text":"String","preciseIdentifier":"s:SS","kind":"typeIdentifier"},{"kind":"text","text":" { "},{"text":"get","kind":"keyword"},{"text":" }","kind":"text"}]}]},{"kind":"parameters","parameters":[{"content":[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"The key to use to get a value"}]}],"name":"key"}]},{"content":[{"anchor":"overview","text":"Overview","level":2,"type":"heading"},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"In fact if it seems some rules are missing, or weight are not managed, if the font family only is returned"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"the user has an higher probability to use the expected font. Because if a mashup of family name and weight is returned"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"it can produce a PostScript identifier not available, so not usable, so implying a fallback to default system font like "},{"type":"emphasis","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"San Francisco"}]},{"type":"text","text":"."},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"Because PostScript identifiers in most of cases do not have whitespaces, remove them."}]},{"syntax":"swift","code":["    \/\/ Given a dictionary with one value","    let myDict: PostScriptFontNamesMap = [PSFNMK(\"Arial\", Font.Weight.bold): \"Aria-BoldMT\"]","","    \/\/ The given value is returned if the key exists","    let keyExists = myDict[PSFNMK(\"Arial\", Font.Weight.bold)] \/\/ Arial-BoldMT","","    \/\/ But if the key does not exist, the only the key is returned","    let keyDoesNotExist = myDict[PSFNMK(\"Luciole\", Font.Weight.bold)] \/\/ Luciole"],"type":"codeListing"}],"kind":"content"}],"kind":"symbol","schemaVersion":{"patch":0,"minor":3,"major":0},"sections":[],"hierarchy":{"paths":[["doc:\/\/OUDSFoundations\/documentation\/OUDSFoundations","doc:\/\/OUDSFoundations\/documentation\/OUDSFoundations\/Swift","doc:\/\/OUDSFoundations\/documentation\/OUDSFoundations\/Swift\/Dictionary"]]},"abstract":[{"text":"If there is no value for the given ","type":"text"},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"key"},{"text":", returns the description of this key,","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"i.e.font family name without the font weight in the end and without whitespaces."}],"variants":[{"traits":[{"interfaceLanguage":"swift"}],"paths":["\/documentation\/oudsfoundations\/swift\/dictionary\/subscript(orkey:)"]}],"identifier":{"interfaceLanguage":"swift","url":"doc:\/\/OUDSFoundations\/documentation\/OUDSFoundations\/Swift\/Dictionary\/subscript(orKey:)"},"metadata":{"extendedModule":"Swift","modules":[{"relatedModules":["Swift"],"name":"Foundations"}],"roleHeading":"Instance Subscript","title":"subscript(orKey:)","symbolKind":"subscript","fragments":[{"text":"subscript","kind":"keyword"},{"text":"(","kind":"text"},{"text":"orKey","kind":"externalParam"},{"kind":"text","text":" _: "},{"kind":"typeIdentifier","text":"Key"},{"kind":"text","text":") -> "},{"kind":"typeIdentifier","preciseIdentifier":"s:SS","text":"String"}],"conformance":{"conformancePrefix":[{"text":"Conforms when","type":"text"}],"availabilityPrefix":[{"text":"Available when","type":"text"}],"constraints":[{"code":"Key","type":"codeVoice"},{"type":"text","text":" is "},{"code":"PostScriptFontNamesMapKey","type":"codeVoice"},{"text":" and ","type":"text"},{"code":"Value","type":"codeVoice"},{"text":" is ","type":"text"},{"code":"String","type":"codeVoice"},{"type":"text","text":"."}]},"role":"symbol","externalID":"s:SD15OUDSFoundationsAA25PostScriptFontNamesMapKeyVRszSSRs_rlE02orG0SSAC_tcip"},"references":{"doc://OU